<section>
<h1>
<span>Appendix B </span>CSS</h1>
<div></div>

<div id="p1">
<p><span>This section is non-normative.</span></p>
</div>
<div id="p2">
<p>Some <code>mstyle</code> attributes follow the standard CSS inheritance and can be
easily implemented by mapping them to CSS properties. Five new CSS properties
would be needed for that purpose and are proposed in section
<a href="S2.html#SS3.SSS1" title="2.3.1 Properties ‣ 2.3 CSS Styling ‣ 2 Relation with other technologies ‣ MathML in HTML5 - Implementation Note"><span>2.3.1</span></a>:</p>
</div>
<div id="p3">
<ol id="I15">
<li id="I15.i1"> 
<div id="I15.i1.p1">
<p><span>mathml-math-style</span> (cf table <a href="S2.html#SS3.SSS1" title="2.3.1 Properties ‣ 2.3 CSS Styling ‣ 2 Relation with other technologies ‣ MathML in HTML5 - Implementation Note"><span>2.3.1</span></a>)</p>
</div>
</li>
<li id="I15.i2"> 
<div id="I15.i2.p1">
<p><span>mathml-math-variant</span> (cf table <a href="S2.html#SS3.SSS1.tab1" title="2.3.1 Properties ‣ 2.3 CSS Styling ‣ 2 Relation with other technologies ‣ MathML in HTML5 - Implementation Note"><span>2.3.1</span></a>)</p>
</div>
</li>
<li id="I15.i3"> 
<div id="I15.i3.p1">
<p><span>mathml-script-level</span> (cf table <a href="S2.html#SS3.SSS1.tab2" title="2.3.1 Properties ‣ 2.3 CSS Styling ‣ 2 Relation with other technologies ‣ MathML in HTML5 - Implementation Note"><span>2.3.1</span></a>)</p>
</div>
</li>
<li id="I15.i4"> 
<div id="I15.i4.p1">
<p><span>mathml-script-size-multiplier</span> (cf table <a href="S2.html#SS3.SSS1.tab3" title="2.3.1 Properties ‣ 2.3 CSS Styling ‣ 2 Relation with other technologies ‣ MathML in HTML5 - Implementation Note"><span>2.3.1</span></a>)</p>
</div>
</li>
<li id="I15.i5"> 
<div id="I15.i5.p1">
<p><span>mathml-script-min-size</span> (cf table <a href="S2.html#SS3.SSS1.tab4" title="2.3.1 Properties ‣ 2.3 CSS Styling ‣ 2 Relation with other technologies ‣ MathML in HTML5 - Implementation Note"><span>2.3.1</span></a>)</p>
</div>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div id="p4">
<p>In practice, only the first three properties are involved (either implicity
or explicitly) in documents with MathML content while the default values are
almost always used for the two last properties. Hence, these three first
properties seem the most important to consider.
</p>
</div>
</section>
